    <div class="callout">
      <strong>The short version:</strong> Refundable tickets get refunded. Non-refundable tickets are bound by the airline's fare rules. Our service fee is refundable within 24 hours of booking if the airline ticket itself is also refunded.
    </div>

    <h2><span class="num">01.</span>Understanding Your Ticket</h2>
    <p>Every flight ticket carries a <strong>fare type</strong> that determines refund eligibility. You'll see this clearly labelled at the time of booking:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fully refundable:</strong> Cancel any time before departure for a full refund minus any airline service fee</li>
      <li><strong>Partially refundable:</strong> Refundable minus a cancellation penalty (varies by airline and fare class)</li>
      <li><strong>Non-refundable:</strong> No cash refund; may be eligible for travel credit minus a change fee</li>
      <li><strong>Basic / Light fares:</strong> Typically no refund and no credit; review carefully before booking</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><span class="num">02.</span>24-Hour Risk-Free Window</h2>
    <p>For most bookings made through FlightDojo on flights departing the United States, you may cancel within <strong>24 hours of booking for a full refund</strong>, provided the booking was made at least 7 days before departure. This complies with US Department of Transportation regulations.</p>
    <p>Bookings made through FlightDojo for other jurisdictions may have similar protections depending on local law.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">03.</span>Cancellation by the Airline</h2>
    <p>If the operating airline cancels your flight, you are entitled to either:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A full refund of the ticket price, regardless of the fare type, or</li>
      <li>Rebooking on the next available flight at no extra cost</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For flights covered by EU Regulation 261/2004 or similar consumer protection laws, you may also be entitled to compensation. FlightDojo will assist with claims at no charge.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">04.</span>Schedule Changes</h2>
    <p>If the airline changes your flight time by more than 4 hours, departs from a different airport, or removes a stop you were counting on, you may request a free refund or rebooking.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">05.</span>FlightDojo Service Fees</h2>
    <p>If you cancel a booking and receive a full refund from the airline, our service fee will also be refunded. If only a partial airline refund applies, our service fee is non-refundable as we have already provided the booking service.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">06.</span>How to Request a Refund</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Log in to your FlightDojo account and locate the booking under "My Trips"</li>
      <li>Click "Request Refund" and follow the prompts</li>
      <li>Alternatively, email <a href="mailto:refunds@flightdojo.it.com">refunds@flightdojo.it.com</a> with your booking reference</li>
      <li>Our team will confirm eligibility within 24 hours and submit the request to the airline</li>
    </ol>

    <h2><span class="num">07.</span>Processing Times</h2>
    <p>Refund processing depends on the airline and your payment method:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Credit/debit cards:</strong> 7–14 business days after airline approval</li>
      <li><strong>Bank transfers:</strong> 14–30 business days</li>
      <li><strong>Travel credit/vouchers:</strong> Typically issued within 5 business days</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Some refunds may take up to 12 weeks during peak travel disruption periods. We will keep you informed of progress.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">08.</span>Non-Refundable Components</h2>
    <p>The following are generally non-refundable regardless of fare type:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Seat selection fees once travel has commenced</li>
      <li>Baggage fees for journeys already taken</li>
      <li>Travel insurance premiums (refer to insurer's terms)</li>
      <li>Cancellation fees imposed by the airline</li>
    </ul>

    <h2><span class="num">09.</span>Special Circumstances</h2>
    <h3>Medical emergencies</h3>
    <p>Many airlines offer compassionate refunds for serious illness, hospitalisation, or bereavement. We can help you submit documentation and advocate on your behalf.</p>
    <h3>Travel advisories</h3>
    <p>Government-issued travel warnings or border closures may make certain bookings eligible for refund or credit. Contact us as soon as possible.</p>
    <h3>Visa denial</h3>
    <p>Some flexible fares cover visa denial. Most do not. Review fare rules before booking if this is a concern.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">10.</span>Chargebacks</h2>
    <p>We strongly prefer to resolve refund issues directly. Initiating a chargeback before contacting us can delay resolution by weeks. Please reach out to <a href="mailto:refunds@flightdojo.it.com">refunds@flightdojo.it.com</a> first.</p>

    <h2><span class="num">11.</span>Disputes</h2>
    <p>If you disagree with a refund decision, you may escalate to our customer success team. If we cannot reach agreement, you may seek resolution through the relevant aviation consumer authority in your jurisdiction.</p>

